job.description:
About us:&amp;nbsp;Wiser Solutions is a suite of in-store and eCommerce intelligence&amp;nbsp;and execution tools. We're on a mission to enable brands, retailers, and retail channel partners to gather intelligence and automate actions to optimize pricing, marketing, and operations initiatives, both in-store and online. Our Commerce Execution Suite is available globally.&amp;nbsp;   Position Summary:We are building the&amp;nbsp;next generation data science technology on top of massive amounts of structured and unstructured data.&amp;nbsp;We are a fast-paced, dynamic (and fun) organization with many unique and interesting technology challenges. You’ll get to help build our&amp;nbsp;machine learning and&amp;nbsp;data science stack, design our architecture,&amp;nbsp;train,&amp;nbsp;and deploy models,&amp;nbsp;fix things when they break and do it with smart, down-to-earth people that enjoy having fun while working together.&amp;nbsp;   Essential Functions:  - Design and build software systems for machine learning,&amp;nbsp;model inference&amp;nbsp;and analytics&amp;nbsp;   
  - Expand machine learning based intelligence capability of Wiser Data Platform&amp;nbsp;by training models and deploying then for plethora of use cases&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;   
  - Partner closely with other scientists&amp;nbsp;and engineers&amp;nbsp;on the team to develop algorithms and drive key product initiatives&amp;nbsp;   
  - Develop scalable, maintainable, high-quality production code to operationalize developed algorithms and models   
  - Work with Engineering and Product Management to identify&amp;nbsp;modeling&amp;nbsp;use-cases&amp;nbsp;   
  - Present your research and insights to all levels of the company as well as academia&amp;nbsp;   
  - Maintain regular and reliable work attendance&amp;nbsp;   
   Skills and Qualifications:&amp;nbsp;  - BS/MS/PhD&amp;nbsp;degree&amp;nbsp;in&amp;nbsp;Computer Science/Statistics/Data Science/Machine Learning&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;other&amp;nbsp;related quantitative field&amp;nbsp;   
  - At least 2-3 years of experience in heavily&amp;nbsp;coding-oriented&amp;nbsp;software- and/or data-science-role&amp;nbsp;where you built and deployed systems and trained and deployed models. This is a hands-on role where you will be touching all elements of the&amp;nbsp;system including data,&amp;nbsp;server&amp;nbsp;and model deployment layers&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;   
  - Must have significant background in Object-Oriented Design, assessing algorithm runtime and memory complexity and software building paradigms&amp;nbsp;   
  - Experience with feature engineering, imputation&amp;nbsp;methods, feature selection and input sampling for large datasets&amp;nbsp;   
  - Knowledge of machine learning and data mining techniques in one or more areas of statistical modeling,&amp;nbsp;supervised and unsupervised learning,&amp;nbsp;regression analysis, time-series prediction,&amp;nbsp;tree-based&amp;nbsp;models,&amp;nbsp;Bayesian modeling, deep learning,&amp;nbsp;NLP, computer vision&amp;nbsp;   
  - Strong coding skills and ability to develop&amp;nbsp;model&amp;nbsp;prototypes&amp;nbsp;using open-source tools in Python (scikit-learn,&amp;nbsp;xgboost,&amp;nbsp;tensorflow)&amp;nbsp;   
  - Familiarity with creating data pipelines and providing feed-and-care of models&amp;nbsp;   
  - Ability to establish runtime and memory&amp;nbsp;requirements/constraints of machine learning and data science algorithms&amp;nbsp;   
  - Understanding of tradeoffs between model’s statistical and deployment runtime performance&amp;nbsp;   
  - Familiarity with containers and commonly used techniques for deployment of models designed to generate predictions near-real-time&amp;nbsp;   
  - Experience with dynamic pricing strategy or time-series data is a strong plus&amp;nbsp;   
  - Ability to effectively work in Unix-based environment (Linux, MacOS etc.)&amp;nbsp;   
  - Familiarity with&amp;nbsp;Jupyter,&amp;nbsp;Spark a strong plus&amp;nbsp;   
  - Familiarity with A/B testing a plus&amp;nbsp;   
  - Familiarity with reinforcement learning a plus&amp;nbsp;   
   Other Characteristics:&amp;nbsp;  - Strong communication skills and ability to work effectively independently and in teams (local and distributed)&amp;nbsp;   
  - Intellectually curious, with a passion for continuous learning and growing professionally&amp;nbsp;   
  - Ability to multi-task, prioritize, work well in an interrupt driven environment, show initiative and respond quickly in a fast-paced environment.&amp;nbsp;   
  - Possess a strong work ethic and proactive approach to problem solving
